import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

countries = list(fifa_data['Nationality'].value_counts()[:40].index)
count = list(fifa_data['Nationality'].value_counts()[:40].values)

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(16, 9))

ax.bar(countries, count, color='teal')
ax.set_title('Each Nationality Player Count')
ax.set_xlabel('Country')
ax.set_ylabel('Count')
ax.set_xticklabels(countries, rotation='vertical')

plt.show()

In [31]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

top_20_countries = fifa_data['Nationality'].value_counts().head(20).index.to_list()
avg_scores = []
for country in top_20_countries:
    avg_score = fifa_data.loc[fifa_data['Nationality'] == country]['Overall'].mean()
    avg_scores.append(avg_score)

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 5))

ax.bar(top_20_countries, avg_scores, color='tomato')
ax.set_title('Average Score of Players Belonging to Different Countries')
ax.set_xlabel('Country')
ax.set_ylabel('Average Score')
ax.set_xticklabels(top_20_countries, rotation='vertical')
ax.set_ylim([0, 100])

plt.show()
